Class ArgumentTypeInfer

java.lang.Object
lanat.ArgumentTypeInfer
public final class ArgumentTypeInfer extends Object

Argument Type Inferring

Handles inferring argument types for specified types. This is used mostly for defining Arguments in CommandTemplates.

Example:

When defining an Argument, like this: 


 @Argument.Define
 public Double[] numbers;

In this case, get(Class) is called with the type Double[], which will return a TupleArgumentType instance ready to be used for that value type: 

new TupleArgumentType(Range.AT_LEAST_ONE, new DoubleArgumentType()).
